{"id": "EUVD-2020-12354", "enisaUuid": "142bcddc-f6f0-3eef-89c0-9848b09859f2", "description": "An elevation of privilege vulnerability exists in the way that the Windows Graphics Device Interface (GDI) handles objects in memory. An attacker who successfully exploited this vulnerability could run arbitrary code in kernel mode. An attacker could then install programs; view, change, or delete data; or create new accounts with full user rights.\nTo exploit this vulnerability, an attacker would first have to log on to the system. An attacker could then run a specially crafted application that could exploit the vulnerability and take control of an affected system.\nThe update addresses the vulnerability by correcting how GDI handles objects in memory and by preventing instances of unintended user-mode privilege elevation.\n", "datePublished": "2020-08-17T19:13:08", "dateUpdated": "2024-08-04T06:39:09", "baseScore": 7.8, "baseScoreVersion": "3.1", "baseScoreVector": "CVSS:3.1/AV:L/AC:L/PR:L/UI:N/S:U/C:H/I:H/A:H/E:P/RL:O/RC:C", "references": ["https://portal.msrc.microsoft.com/en-US/security-guidance/advisory/CVE-2020-1480"], "aliases": ["CVE-2020-1480"], "assigner": "microsoft", "epss": 0.54, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "03f1e80c-8df0-39ce-a666-22645d0bc0a9", "product": {"name": "Windows 10 Version 2004"}, "product_version": "10.0.0 <publication"}, {"id": "062d0ed5-f137-3704-afa6-f40283b4bd81", "product": {"name": "Windows 10 Version 1809"}, "product_version": "10.0.0 <publication"}, {"id": "21490ac2-93ef-32c7-9180-fcbf109a9e8a", "product": {"name": "Windows Server version 2004"}, "product_version": "10.0.0 <publication"}, {"id": "2a45b0ef-548b-3fa9-85cb-fce751219198", "product": {"name": "Windows 10 Version 1909"}, "product_version": "10.0.0 <publication"}, {"id": "7f37a76c-243e-34a2-b25c-7aa5e4c46b06", "product": {"name": "Windows Server 2019 (Server Core installation)"}, "product_version": "10.0.0 <publication"}, {"id": "83d9019b-859c-3d9b-ac10-5a5c66b5f218", "product": {